ons of law and literature and by doing so, offers new insights into two of the foundational texts of Western culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 4aHomer. 4aIlias. 4aOdyssee. 4aOrestie.  aHomer.  aIliad.  aOdyssey.  aOresteia.0 cEPUBz97831107661720 cprintz978311076593940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311076611040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110766110423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110766110/original  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK